         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden, ¶ 18/7/72 ¶  ¶ The harrassing confusion in my Department, dear Mr Clarke, has been the cause of my apparent discourtesy of not replying to your kind note earlier. ¶  I  ¶ have s...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.07.18</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Marcus Clarke</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">VPRS 5834/PO/2, inward correspondence p. 257, VA 1411 Industrial and Technological Museum, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Garden,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/7/72</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The harrassing confusion in my Department, dear Mr Clarke, has been the cause of my apparent discourtesy of not replying to your kind note earlier.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M. Clarke to M, 9 July 1872 (in this edition as 72-07-09a).</p>
               </note> I <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">have sent the</hi>
               </seg> necessary forms to Miss <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Blyth, for claiming</hi>
               </seg> the amount. When the pictures are framed I will add on a card [the]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS is smudged.</p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">names</hi>
               </seg>, if that meets with your approval.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As regards the other drawings from W.A. it <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">seems to me that they are worth 5/ each</hi>
               </seg> considering that they are original. If however the trustees think that too much, then any smaller sum offered for them might be acceptable to the poor clergyman, who certainly did not make the drawings for earthly gain. I could then bring the offer of the trustees under his notice.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M. Clarke to M, </seg>24 July 1872.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have to thank you much for the 72 copies of lectures. I am ashamed that I came abegging, but I run short, after my own copies, printed on my own expense, proved insufficient.</p>
         </div>
